ðŸ”¹ Objective

In this project, we will build an IoT Digital Notice Board using an ESP8266 and an OLED/LCD display.
The system allows teachers or students to send messages from their phone or PC via Wi-Fi, and the messages will be displayed on the notice board.

ðŸ”¹ Real-Life Application

Schools & colleges â†’ display announcements

Offices â†’ display meeting updates

Shops/businesses â†’ display offers

Homes â†’ display reminders

ðŸ”¹ Components Required
Component	Quantity
ESP8266 (NodeMCU/Wemos D1 Mini)	1
OLED Display (SSD1306, 128Ã—64) OR LCD 16x2 with I2C	1
Jumper wires	As required
Breadboard	1
USB cable	1
ðŸ”¹ Circuit Connection (OLED SSD1306)
OLED Pin	ESP8266 Pin
VCC	3.3V
GND	GND
SDA	D2 (GPIO4)
SCL	D1 (GPIO5)

(If you use LCD 16x2 with I2C, wiring is the same: SDA â†’ D2, SCL â†’ D1)

ðŸ”¹ Working Principle

ESP8266 connects to Wi-Fi.

ESP8266 creates a webpage.

You open the ESP8266â€™s IP address in a browser (Chrome, Edge, Firefox).

Type a message in the webpage â†’ press Send.

ESP8266 receives the message and displays it on the OLED/LCD.

ðŸ”¹ Arduino Code
****************************************************************************************************************************************

#include <ESP8266WiFi.h>
#include <ESP8266WebServer.h>
#include <Wire.h>
#include <Adafruit_GFX.h>
#include <Adafruit_SSD1306.h>

// ------- OLED Setup -------
#define SCREEN_WIDTH 128
#define SCREEN_HEIGHT 64
Adafruit_SSD1306 display(SCREEN_WIDTH, SCREEN_HEIGHT, &Wire, -1);

// ------- Wi-Fi Credentials -------
const char* ssid = "YOUR_WIFI_SSID";       // ðŸ”¹ Enter your Wi-Fi SSID
const char* password = "YOUR_WIFI_PASSWORD"; // ðŸ”¹ Enter your Wi-Fi Password

// ------- Web Server -------
ESP8266WebServer server(80);
String message = "Welcome!";

void handleRoot() {
  String html = "<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><meta charset='UTF-8'><title>Digital Notice Board</title>";
  html += "<style>body{font-family:Arial;text-align:center;background:#f0f0f0;}";
  html += "h2{color:#333;}input[type=text]{width:80%;padding:10px;font-size:18px;}";
  html += "button{padding:10px 20px;margin-top:10px;font-size:16px;}</style></head><body>";
  html += "<h2>ESP8266 Digital Notice Board</h2>";
  html += "<form action='/send' method='GET'>";
  html += "<input type='text' name='msg' placeholder='Enter message here'><br>";
  html += "<button type='submit'>Send to Display</button>";
  html += "</form>";
  html += "<p><b>Current Message:</b><br>" + message + "</p>";
  html += "</body></html>";

  server.send(200, "text/html", html);
}

void handleSend() {
  if (server.hasArg("msg")) {
    message = server.arg("msg");
    // Display on OLED
    display.clearDisplay();
    display.setTextSize(1);
    display.setTextColor(SSD1306_WHITE);
    display.setCursor(0, 10);
    display.println(message);
    display.display();
  }
  handleRoot();
}

void setup() {
  Serial.begin(115200);

  // Start OLED
  if (!display.begin(SSD1306_SWITCHCAPVCC, 0x3C)) {
    Serial.println(F("SSD1306 allocation failed"));
    for (;;);
  }
  display.clearDisplay();
  display.setTextSize(1);
  display.setTextColor(SSD1306_WHITE);
  display.setCursor(0, 10);
  display.println("Connecting WiFi...");
  display.display();

  // Wi-Fi
  WiFi.begin(ssid, password);
  Serial.print("Connecting to WiFi");
  while (WiFi.status() != WL_CONNECTED) {
    delay(500);
    Serial.print(".");
  }
  Serial.println("\nConnected!");
  Serial.print("IP Address: ");
  Serial.println(WiFi.localIP());

  display.clearDisplay();
  display.setCursor(0, 10);
  display.println("WiFi Connected!");
  display.println(WiFi.localIP());
  display.display();

  // Web server routes
  server.on("/", handleRoot);
  server.on("/send", handleSend);
  server.begin();
  Serial.println("Web server started");
}

void loop() {
  server.handleClient();
}

*******************************************************************************************************************************************8
ðŸ”¹ Steps for Students

Upload the code to ESP8266 (donâ€™t forget to edit Wi-Fi SSID & Password).

Open Serial Monitor â†’ Note the IP address.

Open Chrome â†’ Type:

http://<your_IP_address>


Example: http://192.168.1.45

Enter a message â†’ Press Send.

Message will instantly show on the OLED/LCD screen.

ðŸ”¹ Output Example

Webpage shows:
"ESP8266 Digital Notice Board"
with a textbox + Send button.

When you type "Good Morning Students" â†’ It will appear on the OLED/LCD screen.

ðŸ”¹ Key Learning

Students learn IoT concepts (ESP8266 + Wi-Fi).

How to host a webpage on ESP8266.

Sending & receiving data between browser and hardware.

Displaying data on a hardware screen (OLED/LCD).
